      problemTitle: "Why do wrinkles form?",
      problemBody: "<p>Wrinkles result from a complex process. With age, the production of collagen and elastin decreases – the proteins that give skin firmness and elasticity. Simultaneously, subcutaneous fat thins and skin loses volume. This is natural and nothing to be ashamed of.</p><p>But most visible skin aging isn't caused by time but by external factors: UV radiation, pollution, stress, poor sleep, and diet. Together they create oxidative stress – free radicals that break down collagen and damage cellular DNA. Up to 80 percent of facial aging is attributed to sun exposure.</p><p>The anti-aging industry is worth billions and built on unrealistic promises. But real anti-aging isn't about stopping time – it's about protecting skin from unnecessary damage and giving it nourishment to repair itself. It's a marathon, not a sprint.</p>",
